{"type":"message","id":"a399469b","parentId":"0b7b54a1","timestamp":"2026-05-15T07:20:11.952Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_51PXKiM5Tguc1bbt6KOj9953","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"@echo off\r\nchcp 65001 >nul 2>&1\r\nsetlocal\r\n\r\n:: 与 PlatformSwitcher.bat 一致：按本机安装修改 Unity 路径\r\nset \"UNITY_PATH=C:\\Program Files\\Unity\\Hub\\Editor\\2020.3.49f1c1\\Editor\\Unity.exe\"\r\n\r\ncd /d \"%~dp0\" || exit /b 1\r\nset \"PROJECT_PATH=%CD%\"\r\nset \"LOG_FILE=%PROJECT_PATH%\\BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log\"\r\n\r\nif not exist \"%UNITY_PATH%\" (\r\n    echo [ERROR] 未找到 Unity.exe，请编辑本 bat 中的 UNITY_PATH。\r\n    exit /b 1\r\n)\r\n\r\necho [INFO] projectPath=%PROJECT_PATH%\r\necho [INFO] 执行无参 RunHotUpdatePipeline：流水线「热更」的全部有效步骤\r\necho [INFO] log=%LOG_FILE%\r\n\r\n\"%UNITY_PATH%\" -batchmode -quit -nographics -projectPath \"%PROJECT_PATH%\" -executeMethod YYZY.BuildPipeline.BuildPipeline.RunHotUpdatePipeline -logFile \"%LOG_FILE%\"\r\n\r\necho [INFO] Unity 退出码: %ERRORLEVEL%\r\nexit /b %ERRORLEVEL%\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1778829611952}}
{"type":"message","id":"06dc3da7","parentId":"a399469b","timestamp":"2026-05-15T07:20:22.001Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - the bat file runs Unity with the `RunHotUpdatePipeline` method. The log file I checked was from a previous run (65MB, last written 12:40). But the bat file should have just been executed and produced new log output at the end. Let me check if the log file was just updated by checking the last modification time again or looking for more recent entries.\n\nActually, wait - I need to re-examine. The `process list` showed \"No running or recent sessions\", which means the exec finished. The bat file runs Unity which then runs the pipeline and exits. The log was 65MB at 12:40... wait, the current time is 15:19, and the log was last written at 12:40. That's a couple of hours ago. But the exec I just ran should have triggered a new Unity run.\n\nHmm, but the exec output only showed `E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\RunBuildPipelineHotUpdate.bat` - that's just the echo of the path. The bat file itself uses `@echo off` so it suppresses output. The Unity process would have been spawned by the bat file. Let me check if a new Unity.exe ran.\n\nWait, the system is returning exit code 1 because there's no Unity process - that was my Get-Process command returning exit code 1 (no processes found). So it seems like the bat file ran Unity, Unity ran the pipeline, completed, and exited. But the log file shows a last write time of 12:40 which seems old.\n\nActually, wait. Let me re-read carefully. The log file was 65,619,158 bytes at 12:40. But it's now 15:19. So the log hasn't been updated since 12:40. That means either:\n1. The bat file didn't actually produce new output (it ran but Unity wrote to the same log file from a previous run and the timestamp didn't update for some reason), or\n2. The pipeline ran but output is being written somewhere else.\n\nLet me check the exit code of the exec and get more details, and also try running the bat file again and monitor more carefully.\n\nActually, I think there might be a timing issue. The `exec` yieldMs was 15000 (15 seconds), and the `timeout` was 3600 seconds. The bat file ran, launched Unity, and then the exec polled after 15 seconds. Unity might still be running but the exec might have already exited.\n\nLet me check if Unity.exe is actually running right now.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_lcKwDwYpceFZAidJXaRM2826","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Process -Name \"Unity\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Format-Table Id, StartTime, CPU, WorkingSet64 -AutoSize"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":428,"output":619,"cacheRead":13440,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14487,"cost":{"input":0.00005992,"output":0.00017332,"cacheRead":0.00037632,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00060956}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778829611953,"responseId":"b7f45bd9-fd80-4a89-9a37-659044091c80"}}
