{"type":"message","id":"97d03e5e","parentId":"7c0cec50","timestamp":"2026-05-15T07:43:21.394Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No \"Upload\", \"CDN\", \"Success\" entries. The log just ends with SpriteAtlasPacking. This means the second Unity process (PID 23816) was likely building asset bundles for a specific platform and then crashed/exited without completing the full pipeline.\n\nLet me check if the bat file is still running or what happened. Actually, the bat file ran Unity with `-batchmode -quit`, so when Unity exits, the bat exits too. The bat file was launched via Start-Process.\n\nLet me check if there's a Unity process running right now, and also check if the log was appended to the old log file.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_r9h2T0Z3jejfT2UCTRIJ7378","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Process -Name \"Unity\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Id, StartTime, ProcessName; Get-Process | Where-Object { $_.ProcessName -match \"Unity|cmd|bat\" } | Select-Object Id, ProcessName, StartTime"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":899,"output":234,"cacheRead":31360,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32493,"cost":{"input":0.00012586000000000002,"output":0.00006552000000000001,"cacheRead":0.0008780799999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00106946}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778830997786,"responseId":"eaa8b73d-ee98-48a2-93b4-4fe419131428"}}
