{"type":"message","id":"32ce4610","parentId":"c3781597","timestamp":"2026-05-15T07:43:32.585Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No Unity Editor process is running. The bat file process seems to have completed. Let me check the bat's log for the exit code by looking at the end of the BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log more carefully. Maybe the log was overwritten or truncated.\n\nWait - the log file is 37,605,732 bytes and was last modified at 15:34:26. The second Unity process (23816) started at 15:34:31. So the log was last modified BEFORE the second Unity process started. This means the second Unity process was using the SAME log file, either overwriting or appending to it. And when it exited, the log still shows the same timestamp from 15:34:26.\n\nActually, maybe the second Unity process (23816) wasn't related to the bat file at all. Maybe it was just the Unity Hub or something else. Let me check what process launched PID 23816.\n\nActually, I think I need to just look at the logs more carefully. Let me check the beginning of the log for this run's timestamp. The log file from the hotupdate pipeline shows the pipeline starting. Let me search for \"RunHotUpdatePipeline\" in the log and see the timestamps around it.\n\nWait—I already know from the first batch that the PID 17676 ran at 15:20:56 with the log growing to 37MB. The last line written in the log shows SpriteAtlasPacking, with the last write time at 15:34:26.\n\nNow PID 23816 started at 15:34:31 but I didn't see its output in the log. This might be because:\n1. PID 23816 was the old Unity Editor reopening normally (not from the bat)\n2. The bat's Unity finished its pipeline successfully at 15:34:26 and the bat exited\n3. PID 23816 is a completely unrelated Unity process\n\nGiven the log ended with SpriteAtlasPacking at 15:34:26 and the bat file runs `-batchmode -quit`, I think the first Unity process (17676) ran until 15:34:26, then exited. The bat then checked `%ERRORLEVEL%` and exited. PID 23816 is unrelated.\n\nBUT - the log doesn't have a \"Success\" or \"Failed\" message from the pipeline. It just ends mid-build of asset bundles. This shouldn't happen if the pipeline completed successfully.\n\nLet me look at more of the log around the area just before the SpriteAtlasPacking entries to see what was happening.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_tZZHeKeUgo5lPA1kZIUb2077","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Content \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log\" -Tail 80 | Select-String -NotMatch \"SpriteAtlasPacking|Player size statistics|Total compressed\" -SimpleMatch"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":293,"output":636,"cacheRead":32384,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33313,"cost":{"input":0.000041020000000000004,"output":0.00017808,"cacheRead":0.0009067519999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0011258519999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778831002294,"responseId":"1aca8828-77fb-4660-91de-8888b5fa0cc5"}}
