{"type":"message","id":"d5cb86ac","parentId":"cad2570b","timestamp":"2026-05-15T07:43:44.600Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The log file ends with only SpriteAtlasPacking lines - no pipeline completion message, no upload message, nothing. This suggests the Unity process crashed or was killed during the asset bundle building stage.\n\nActually, I think I may have been looking at the old run's log. Let me verify. The log file was 65MB at 12:40 before I ran the pipeline. After running, it's 37MB. That means the new run OVERWROTE the old log! The 37MB log is from the NEW run, not the old one. The Unity command writes to the same file, replacing it (since Unity uses the `-logFile` parameter which creates a new file).\n\nSo the log shows:\n1. The pipeline started around 15:20\n2. It went through Lua merge, compilation\n3. Then started building asset bundles with SpriteAtlasPacking\n4. The log ends abruptly at SpriteAtlasPacking\n\nThis means the build failed or crashed during the asset bundle building stage. The Unity process (17676) was running, it was building bundles, and then it crashed.\n\nBut then PID 23816 started at 15:34 - that was a new Unity process. Let me check if it was related to the bat file or something else. Actually, looking back at the bat file output:\n\n```\n[INFO] projectPath=E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\n[INFO] 鎵ц鏃犲弬 RunHotUpdatePipeline锛氭祦按绾裤€愮儹鏇淬€戠殑鍏ㄩ儴鏈夋晥姝ラ\n[INFO] log=E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log\n```\n\nThis is the bat's echo output. Then it runs Unity. Unity's output goes to the log file, not stdout. So we wouldn't see Unity's output in the PowerShell console.\n\nWhen I checked at 15:34, Unity PID 17676 had exited, and PID 23816 had started. But what launched PID 23816?\n\nActually, maybe the pipeline itself launches a new Unity process for building for a different platform. The pipeline might run multiple stages:\n1. First Unity process: does Lua merge / preparation\n2. Second Unity process: builds asset bundles for a specific platform\n\nWhen the first Unity exits, the bat exits too. Then PID 23816 might be from something else (like Unity Hub auto-reopening the project, or the previous Unity Editor coming back).\n\nHmm, but actually, the bat file says `-batchmode -quit`, so when Unity exits, the bat checks the error code and exits. There's no loop or multiple invocations in the bat.\n\nLet me look at the beginning of the log to see if it starts fresh or if it shows our current run.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_6PMVvoPbZ9RHL81kDyWQ2830","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Content \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log\" -Head 30"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":941,"output":690,"cacheRead":33280,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34911,"cost":{"input":0.00013174,"output":0.0001932,"cacheRead":0.00093184,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0012567799999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778831013638,"responseId":"f38f8f61-42b4-4f79-ab99-cfdda9917506"}}
