{"type":"message","id":"27b8b888","parentId":"8d576951","timestamp":"2026-05-15T07:44:47.337Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, now I can confirm:\n1. The correct Unity was used (`2020.3.49f1\\Editor\\Unity.exe`)\n2. The correct execute method was called (`YYZY.BuildPipeline.BuildPipeline.RunHotUpdatePipeline`)\n3. The command line is correct\n\nThe pipeline ran, did some work, but the log ends at line 321,988 with no cleanup/exit messages. The SpriteAtlasPacking entries that I saw in the Tail weren't appearing in the Index selection because they might be at different line numbers than I thought.\n\nWait, I counted lines:\n- `Select-Object -Index (321975..321988)` showed lines 321,975 through 321,988\n- These last 14 lines show Lua compilation and stack traces\n- The file ends at line 321,988\n\nBut earlier when I did `-Tail 50`, the last 50 lines showed SpriteAtlasPacking... Something doesn't add up.\n\nOh wait, maybe the file was modified between the two reads! The file was last written at 15:34:26, but when I ran the last read, it might have been later.\n\nActually no, let me just check again what's at the very end of the file right now.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_ENFRIwgFuFj6lUpXfKEH7188","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Item \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log\" | Select-Object Length, LastWriteTime; $lines = Get-Content \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log\"; Write-Host \"Total lines: $($lines.Count)\"; $lines[-5..-1]"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":452,"output":395,"cacheRead":40192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41039,"cost":{"input":0.00006328,"output":0.0001106,"cacheRead":0.001125376,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.001299256}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778831081645,"responseId":"d5f61e1e-12cd-4e74-951e-2507ea10d2f2"