{"type":"message","id":"7b170398","parentId":"549f0314","timestamp":"2026-05-15T07:44:57.330Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now it shows 359,704 lines, not 321,988 lines! The file grew while I was reading it. And the last lines are indeed SpriteAtlasPacking.\n\nSo the file has 359,704 lines, last written at 15:34:26, and ends with SpriteAtlasPacking. The Unity process that was writing to this file exited (was killed/crashed) at 15:34:26.\n\nBut the log shows the file was 37,605,732 bytes at 15:34:26 - that's 37.6 MB. And the earlier check showed the same - 37,605,732 bytes at 15:34:26. So the file hasn't changed since Unity exited.\n\nLet me look at what the very last step in the pipeline was - it was Lua Merge step. From the stack trace, it calls `PipelineCreateBundle` -> `PipelineBuildAssetBundle` -> `MergeLua` -> `Generate`. So the last operation was Lua data generation.\n\nAfter the Lua merge, the next step was \"Build Asset Bundles\" (which is what produces SpriteAtlasPacking). The pipeline was building asset bundles when it stopped.\n\nBut wait, there are no cleanup messages. Unity's normal exit sequence includes \"Cleanup mono\" and other messages. The absence of these means Unity didn't exit normally - it was either killed externally or crashed.\n\nLet me check the Windows Application Event Log for Unity crash events.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_C0nM3lmQwFo3fpxSi5aQ7259","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-WinEvent -LogName Application -MaxEvents 50 2>$null | Where-Object { $_.ProviderName -like \"*Unity*\" -or ($_.Message -like \"*Unity*\" -and $_.LevelDisplayName -eq \"Error\") } | Select-Object TimeCreated, Id, LevelDisplayName, Message | Format-Table -AutoSize -Wrap"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":188,"output":428,"cacheRead":40960,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41576,"cost":{"input":0.00002632000