{"type":"message","id":"fad74376","parentId":"6bab47ab","timestamp":"2026-05-15T07:45:25.906Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, the spawn UNKNOWN error when trying to use ProcessStartInfo. Let me not run the bat again - the pipeline already ran.\n\nLet me recap what happened:\n1. Fixed the Unity path in the bat file (`2020.3.49f1c1` → `2020.3.49f1`)\n2. Ran the bat file via Start-Process with -RedirectStandardOutput\n3. The bat started Unity (PID 17676 at 15:20:56)\n4. Unity ran the pipeline - started with Lua merge, then moved to BuildAssetBundles\n5. The pipeline was building asset bundles (SpriteAtlasPacking) \n6. The log file grew to 37,605,732 bytes (359,704 lines) at 15:34:26\n7. Unity exited PID 17676\n8. A second Unity process (PID 23816) appeared at 15:34:31 but this might have been unrelated\n9. Now there are no Unity processes running\n\nThe log ends abruptly with no pipeline completion message. This is suspicious.\n\nActually, wait - let me re-read the original bat file output I got earlier:\n\n```\n[INFO] projectPath=E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\n[INFO] 鎵ц鏃犲弬 RunHotUpdatePipeline锛氭祦按绾裤€愮儹鏇淬€戠殑鍏ㄩ儴鏈夋晥姝ラ\n[INFO] log=E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log\n```\n\nThen Unity was launched. The bat file then waits for Unity to finish, then prints:\n```\necho [INFO] Unity 退出码: %ERRORLEVEL%\nexit /b %ERRORLEVEL%\n```\n\nBut we never saw this output! The Start-Process with -RedirectStandardOutput should have captured it, but the bat file itself only has 6 echo statements and the process was cut short (the bat was running Unity which was taking a long time).\n\nActually, the Unity process (17676) ran from 15:20:56 to sometime around 15:34 (about 13 minutes). During this time, it was building asset bundles. The log ends at SpriteAtlasPacking.\n\nThen Unity exited, and the bat printed \"Unity 退出码: ...\" and returned.\n\nBut then PID 23816 started at 15:34:31. That was 5 seconds after the log stopped. This is likely a new Unity Editor instance being started by something - maybe Unity Hub, or maybe the user opened Unity manually.\n\nActually, now I think about it more carefully - perhaps PID 23816 was the start of a second stage of the pipeline. Let me check if the bat file or the pipeline launches multiple Unity processes for different platforms. But the bat only has a single Unity invocation.\n\nWait - I also checked earlier:\n```\nGet-Process | Where-Object { $_.ProcessName -match \"Unity|cmd|bat\" }\n```\nAnd found `cmd` process from 10:19:54. That's a command prompt window from the morning, not related.\n\nLet me try one more thing - search the log for the word \"error\" or \"exception\" near the end, and see if there's an out-of-memory or disk-full error.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_1Vnplbx8S1e2SuKQbNcE9042","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Select-String -Path \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log\" -Pattern \"out of memory|outofmemory|disk full|diskfull|IOException"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"aborted","timestamp":1778831114184,"responseId":"03afa199-17cd-48c1-a2e4-93e3d8866a8d","errorMessage":"Request was aborted"}}
