{"type":"message","id":"d74f3a93","parentId":"bd0ea32a","timestamp":"2026-05-15T08:31:21.715Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The problem is clear: **\"No valid Unity Editor license found. Please activate your license.\"**\n\nThe license check is failing because:\n1. The licensing client process (\"Unity.Licensing.Client.exe\") is the one bundled with the Unity Editor itself\n2. The license signature is invalid, and the license is \"not active\"\n3. This is the \"headless\" (batchmode) version of the editor which needs activation\n\nThis is a licensing issue. The Unity Editor needs to be activated/authenticated first. The previous run (at 15:20) had a similar license error but showed \"Successfully resolved entitlements\" and continued. Now it's failing.\n\nThe difference might be that the first run used a different licensing client (the Hub's Unity.Licensing.Client.exe with PID 6764), and now the run is using the bundled licensing client (PID 18252).\n\nI need to activate the Unity license. Let me try running Unity with the `-activateLicense` parameter, or better yet, open the Unity Hub to check the license status.\n\nActually wait - the previous failed run (at 15:34 when Unity PID 23816 started and crashed) already had licensing issues. And now the license seems to have expired or been invalidated.\n\nLet me try to activate the license.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_HPXHSCrIzsAoMARMB1F25457","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"\"C:\\Program Files\\Unity\\Hub\\Editor\\2020.3.49f1\\Editor\\Unity.exe\" -batchmode -quit -logFile \"$env:TEMP\\unity_activate.log\" -username \"i@yousanz.com\" -password \"xxxxx\" -serial \"xxxxx\" 2>&1","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":810,"output":397,"cacheRead":43648,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44855,"cost":{"input":0.0001134,"output":0.00011116000000000001,"cacheRead":0.0