{"type":"message","id":"8a4af8dc","parentId":"d014984a","timestamp":"2026-05-15T08:31:50.329Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the options. Let me try to activate a session with the licensing client first. Maybe the license just needs to be refreshed.\n\nActually, looking back at the earlier successful run (at 15:20), the log showed:\n```\n[Licensing::IpcConnector] Successfully connected to the License Client on channel: \"LicenseClient-yyzypublic\"\n[Licensing::Client] Error: Code 1 while verifying Licensing Client signature\n...\n[Licensing::Client] Successfully resolved entitlements\n[Licensing::Module] Serial number assigned to: \"F4-H1R5-BQNV-8DQZ-Q4V2-XXXX\"\n```\n\nSo it used the license with serial \"F4-H1R5-BQNV-8DQZ-Q4V2-XXXX\". And the licensing client was the Hub's version (PID 6764).\n\nIn the current run, the licensing client is the bundled version (PID 18252 in the first attempt, PID 17288 in the second) and it's saying \"Cannot load ULF license: The digital signature is invalid.\"\n\nI think the issue might be that the bundled licensing client is trying to load a different license file than the Hub's. Let me try to return the ULF license and re-activate it, or try a different approach.\n\nLet me check the license serial from the earlier log and try to re-activate:","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_lBBEZ9fvYchtZ9O7AfuQ7088","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Try to return the current license and re-acquire\n# First let's see what license files exist\nGet-ChildItem \"$env:PROGRAMDATA\\Unity\\*.ulf\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Name, Length, LastWriteTime, FullName\nWrite-Host \"---\"\n# Check if there's also a legacy license\nGet-ChildItem \"$env:USERPROFILE\\AppData\\Local\\Unity\\*.ulf\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Name, Length, LastWriteTime, FullName"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4