{"type":"message","id":"c6b7f895","parentId":"ea56213b","timestamp":"2026-05-15T08:33:12.627Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's no auth token file in the Unity Hub data. The user needs to re-login to Unity Hub to get a fresh authentication token.\n\nHowever, I can't ask the user to re-login - my job is to run the pipeline. Let me try an alternative approach. Let me check if there's a Unity serial number that we can use to manually activate the license.\n\nActually, looking at the earlier log output from the successful run at 15:20:\n```\n[Licensing::Module] Serial number assigned to: \"F4-H1R5-BQNV-8DQZ-Q4V2-XXXX\"\n```\n\nThe serial is partially redacted. But it still worked because the license client from the Hub (not the bundled one) could connect. Maybe the issue is that the Hub's licensing client isn't running properly.\n\nLet me try restarting the Unity Hub's licensing client.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_pZmMXS27H1jQ6YN1nAzg8010","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Kill any existing licensing client spawned by editor\nGet-Process -Name \"Unity.Licensing.Client\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Where-Object { $_.StartTime -gt (Get-Date \"2026-05-15 16:30:00\") } | Stop-Process -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue; Start-Sleep -Seconds 2\n\n# Check if Hub's licensing client process is already running\n$hubLicProcess = Get-Process -Name \"Unity.Licensing.Client\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Where-Object { (Get-Process -Id $_.Id).StartTime -lt (Get-Date \"2026-05-15 16:30:00\") }\nif ($hubLicProcess) {\n    Write-Host \"Hub's licensing client already running: PID $($hubLicProcess.Id) since $($hubLicProcess.StartTime)\"\n} else {\n    Write-Host \"No Hub licensing client running, trying to start via Unity Hub...\"\n}\n\n# Try to make Unity Hub acquire a new session\n& \"C:\\Program Files\\Unity Hub\\Unity Hub.exe\" -- --headless --acquire-license 2>&1 | Select-String -Pattern \"license|error|success|activated\" -CaseSensitive:$false\n\nWrite-Host \"---Checking Unity Hub licensing...\"\nGet-Process -Name \"Unity.Licensing.Client\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Id, StartTime","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":513,"output":548,"cacheRead":50944,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":52005,"cost":{"input":0.00007182,"output":0.00015344000000000002,"cacheRead":0.001426432,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0016516920000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778833985519,"responseId":"9f756385-8396-401b-915b-3258db74796d"}}
