{"type":"message","id":"db0f66cd","parentId":"a5fea013","timestamp":"2026-05-15T08:33:42.316Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the cloud config - it uses Unity China servers (unity.cn). The user needs to be logged in to Unity Hub to have a valid auth token.\n\nThe problem is likely that the user's Unity Hub session expired or the auth token is invalid. Without the user logging in again, we can't fix this programmatically.\n\nLet me try another approach - maybe we can use the `--username` and `--password` parameters for the licensing client to authenticate. But I don't have the user's Unity credentials.\n\nLet me check if there's an access token in the system that could be used:","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_D9hnu3m8YfcZGixSGqnY1381","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check for any auth tokens in the registry or environment\n$envVar = [Environment]::GetEnvironmentVariable(\"UNITY_AUTH_TOKEN\", \"User\"); \nif ($envVar) { Write-Host \"UNITY_AUTH_TOKEN exists: length=$($envVar.Length)\" } else { Write-Host \"No UNITY_AUTH_TOKEN env var\" }\n\n# Check for Unity License in the registry\n$regPaths = @(\n    \"HKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Unity Technologies\\\",\n    \"HKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\WOW6432Node\\Unity Technologies\\\",\n    \"HKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Unity Technologies\\\"\n)\nforeach ($path in $regPaths) {\n    if (Test-Path $path) {\n        Write-Host \"Registry: $path\"\n        Get-ChildItem $path -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | ForEach-Object { Write-Host \"  $($_.PSPath)\" }\n    }\n}"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":630,"output":363,"cacheRead":53504,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":54497,"cost":{"input":0.0000882,"output":0.00010164000000000001,"cacheRead":0.001498112,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.001687952}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778834017422,"responseId":"5e6f5af2-c771-4a25-bad0-b567c54749ce"}}
