{"type":"message","id":"429ed9e7","parentId":"220899bf","timestamp":"2026-05-15T08:34:17.577Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The files might not actually exist as regular files. The Get-ChildItem might have been showing phantom data, or the files are virtual/cached. This is getting complex.\n\nLet me take a step back. The fundamental problem is the Unity license. Without the user re-authenticating in Unity Hub, we can't run the batchmode pipeline. I need to report this to the user/fail the pipeline.\n\nLet me try one last thing - restart all Unity Hub processes and try again, OR try to run Unity with the `--enable-license-update` flag or similar.\n\nActually, I just remembered - the earlier successful run at 15:20 used the Hub's licensing client. The difference was the LICENSING CLIENT used. When Unity runs, it uses the bundled licensing client. But the Hub's licensing client was already running from before. The key difference might be that the Hub's licensing client could still use the old, cached session.\n\nLet me try re-running the Unity Hub to re-establish the session.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_H2JP5jKzFBgPNiDFkJ598574","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Kill all Unity Hub and licensing processes to force a fresh start\nGet-Process -Name \"Unity Hub\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Stop-Process -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\nGet-Process -Name \"Unity.Licensing.Client\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Stop-Process -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\nStart-Sleep -Seconds 3\n\n# Check if they're gone\nGet-Process -Name \"Unity*\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object ProcessName, Id","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":264,"output":379,"cacheRead":57600,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":58243,"cost":{"input":0.000036960000000000005,"output":0.00010612000000000001,"cacheRead":0.0016128