{"type":"message","id":"fc922581","parentId":"57cca5e1","timestamp":"2026-05-15T08:34:56.297Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Same issue. The Unity Hub is running (many processes, started at 16:34:39) but the Editor still can't get a valid license. The error is \"License is not active (com.unity.editor.headless)\" which means the entitlement-based licensing doesn't include the headless (batchmode) entitlement.\n\nThis is a license activation issue that requires user interaction - the user needs to log into Unity Hub and ensure the license is active for batchmode use.\n\nLet me check one more thing - the earlier version of the Editor.log might show how it was activated before.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_L4zFWDIXgXP8QSGbRgJw2334","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check Editor.log for serial info from earlier runs\nSelect-String -Path \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Unity\\Editor\\Editor.log\" -Pattern \"Serial number|activated|license|entitlement\" -CaseSensitive:$false | Select-Object -Last 10"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":280,"output":227,"cacheRead":59136,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59643,"cost":{"input":0.000039200000000000004,"output":0.00006356000000000001,"cacheRead":0.001655808,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0017585679999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778834092400,"responseId":"930797d2-0832-4e21-a0e6-69f68952250c"}}
