hile updating license\r\n in client (status: Unable to update licenses. Errors: Request (POST https://license.unity.cn/update/poll?cmd=2&tx_id=f\r\nc249ef6822d434a9a4934902bc08af7) failed [400 Bad Request]: Bad ULF signature - suspect foul play,Token not found in cac\r\nhe)\r\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Unity\\Editor\\Editor.log:19:[Licensing::Client] Successfully resolved entitlements\r\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Unity\\Editor\\Editor.log:20:[Licensing::Module] Serial number assigned to: \"F4-H1R5-BQ\r\nNV-8DQZ-Q4V2-XXXX\"\r\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Unity\\Editor\\Editor.log:34:LicenseClient-yyzypublic\r\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Unity\\Editor\\Editor.log:44:AS: AutoStreaming module initializing.[Licensing::Client] \r\nSuccessfully resolved entitlements\r\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Unity\\Editor\\Editor.log:46:[Licensing::Client] Successfully resolved entitlement deta\r\nils\r\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Unity\\Editor\\Editor.log:137:[Licensing::Client] Successfully resolved entitlements\r\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Unity\\Editor\\Editor.log:146:[Licensing::Client] Successfully resolved entitlements\r\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Unity\\Editor\\Editor.log:184:[Licensing::Client] Successfully resolved entitlements\r\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Unity\\Editor\\Editor.log:186:LICENSE SYSTEM [2026515 16:34:54] Unity license informati\r\non is invalid.","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778834097229}}
{"type":"message","id":"3a47beeb","parentId":"89662f5a","timestamp":"2026-05-15T08:35:05.170Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so the Editor.log shows:\n1. The serial is `F4-H1R5-BQNV-8DQZ-Q4V2-XXXX` (the XXXX part is from the log)\n2. \"Bad ULF signature - suspect foul play\" - the signature verification fails\n3. \"LICENSE SYSTEM [2026515 16:34:54] Unity license information is invalid.\" - latest entry\n\nThe license is fundamentally corrupted. The user needs to re-activate Unity. Let me try to return the license via the Editor's bundled licensing client, or try to open Unity GUI once to trigger a re-activation.\n\nActually, let me try a completely different approach - use PowerShell to simulate the Unity Hub login page or use the `--activate-ulf --serial` command with the serial number.\n\nThe serial number is `F4-H1R5-BQNV-8DQZ-Q4V2-XXXX`. The last 4 characters are \"XXXX\" in the log - that's the log's redaction, not the actual serial. The real serial would have actual characters there.\n\nSince I don't have the complete serial, I can't activate this way.\n\nLet me try one final approach - restart the licensing client and force a re-authentication:","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_3Nq7ruwr3cW34pz7JAME2072","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Try the get-license approach using the editor's bundled licensing client\n# First, kill all licensing clients\nGet-Process -Name \"Unity.Licensing.Client\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Stop-Process -Force\nStart-Sleep -Seconds 2\n\n# Start the Hub's licensing client with return-ulf then activate-ulf \n$licClient = \"C:\\Program Files\\Unity Hub\\UnityLicensingClient_V1\\Unity.Licensing.Client.exe\"\n\n# Try return ULF (it will fail but might clear state)\n& $licClient --return-ulf 2>&1\nWrite-Host \"Exit code: $LASTEXITCODE\"\nWrite-Host \"---\"\n\n# Try acquire new ULF\n& $licClient --activate-ulf 2>&1\nWrite-Host \"Exit code: $LASTEXITCODE\"\nWrite-Host \"---\"\n\n# Check if we have a ulf file now\nGet-ChildItem \"$env:PROGRAMDATA\\Unity\\*.ulf\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Name, Length, LastWriteTime","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":612,"output":550,"cacheRead":59520,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60682,"cost":{"input":0.00008568,"output":0.000154,"cacheRead":0.0016665599999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0019062399999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778834097231,"responseId":"c7d735ed-fa06-4e93-b40a-269565c7af15"}}
{"type":"message","id":"3e44b4b7","parentId":"3a47beeb","timestamp":"2026-05-15T08:35:10.572Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_3Nq7ruwr3cW34pz7JAME2072","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"An error occured while trying to return the ULF license. Request (POST https://license.unity.cn/update/poll?cmd=3&tx_id=4e7bb2c595cb41a99deedffe9bf5e6de) failed [400 Bad Request]: Bad ULF signature - suspect foul play (400)\r\nExit code: 28\n---\nUsage: --activate-ulf should be used with --accessToken or --username and --password\r\n*** code: 2\n---\n\r\nName          Length LastWriteTime     \r\n----          ------ -------------     \r\nUnity_lic.ulf   2617 2026/1/14 10:20:12"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":5384,"aggregated":"An error occured while trying to return the ULF license. Request (POST https://license.unity.cn/update/poll?cmd=3&tx_id=4e7bb2c595cb41a99deedffe9bf5e6de) failed [400 Bad Request]: Bad ULF signature - suspect foul play (400)\r\nExit code: 28\n---\nUsage: --activate-ulf should be used with --accessToken or --username and --password\r\nExit code: 2\n---\n\r\nName          Length LastWriteTime     \r\n----          ------ -------------     \r\nUnity_lic.ulf   2617 2026/1/14 10:20:12","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778834110572}}
{"type":"message","id":"a8a181d9","parentId":"3e44b4b7","timestamp":"2026-05-15T08:35:19.537Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The ULF file is back! It must have been recreated by the Unity Hub or the licensing client. But it's the same corrupted file (2617 bytes, same date) - there's probably a backup or cache that restored it.\n\nThe fundamental problem remains: the Unity license with serial `F4-H1R5-BQNV-8DQZ-Q4V2-XXXX` has an invalid digital signature. This could be due to:\n1. The license was activated on a different machine and the signature doesn't match this machine\n2. The license file was tampered with\n3. The Unity license server is having issues\n\nGiven that the previous run at 15:20 DID work (before our pipeline failed mid-build), the license was valid at that point. What changed? The failed pipeline run might have corrupted something.\n\nThe serial from the earlier successful log is partially visible: `F4-H1R5-BQNV-8DQZ-Q4V2-XXXX`. The \"XXXX\" in the log is Unity's log masking, not the real serial. The real serial has proper characters there.\n\nI'm stuck. I need to inform the user that the Unity license needs to be re-activated in Unity Hub before the pipeline can run.\n\nActually, wait. Let me check one more thing - the `-batchmode` flag uses a different license entitlement than the normal GUI mode. Maybe if we open the Unity Editor in GUI mode (even briefly), it would refresh the license.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_fs84zlFh2DzCcz0u9qqz9899","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Try opening Unity Editor in non-batchmode briefly to trigger license refresh\n# Use -createProject to force license check without batchmode\n$unity = \"C:\\Program Files\\Unity\\Hub\\Editor\\2020.3.49f1\\Editor\\Unity.exe\"\n$project = \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\"\n$logFile = \"$env:TEMP\\unity_license_test.log\"\n\n# Start Unity in GUI mode minimized, then kill it after 30 seconds\n$p = Start-Process -FilePath $unity -ArgumentList \"-projectPath `\"$project`\" -logFile `\"$logFile`\"\" -WindowStyle Minimized -PassThru\nWrite-Host \"Started Unity PID: $($p.Id) at $(Get-Date)\"\nStart-Sleep -Seconds 30\nif (!$p.HasExited) {\n    $p.Kill()\n    Write-Host \"Killed Unity after 30 seconds\"\n} else {\n    Write-Host \"Unity exited on its own, code: $($p.ExitCode)\"\n}\n\nWrite-Host \"---Checking log for license status:\"\nSelect-String -Path $logFile -Pattern \"license|activated|entitlement|Serial number|Error\" -CaseSensitive:$false | Select-Object -Last 10","timeout":60,"yieldMs":35000}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":170,"output":663,"cacheRead":60672,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61505,"cost":{"input":0.000023800000000000003,"output":0.00018564000000000002,"cacheRead":0.001698816,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0019082559999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778834110575,"responseId":"6212f523-0632-4b1c-8ff1-5ea5d6d5a8db"}}
{"type":"message","id":"7038db0c","parentId":"a8a181d9","timestamp":"2026-05-15T08:35:50.599Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_fs84zlFh2DzCcz0u9qqz9899","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Started Unity PID: 13664 at 05/15/2026 16:35:20\nKilled Unity after 30 seconds\n---Checking log for license status:\n\r\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\unity_license_test.log:4:[Licensing::Module] Error: LicensingClient has failed v\r\nalidation; ignoring\r\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\unity_license_test.log:11:[Licensing::Module] Successfully connected to Licensin\r\ngClient on channel: \"LicenseClient-yyzypublic\" (connect: 0.00s, validation: 0.02s, handshake: 0.52s)\r\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\unity_license_test.log:12:[Licensing::IpcConnector] Successfully connected to th\r\ne License Notification on channel: \"LicenseClient-yyzypublic-notifications\"\r\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\unity_license_test.log:13:Entitlement-based licensing initiated\r\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\unity_license_test.log:14:[Licensing::Module] Error: Access token is unavailable\r\n; failed to update\r\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\unity_license_test.log:15:[Licensing::Client] Error: Code 500 while processing r\r\nequest (status: Unable to update licenses. Errors: Request (POST https://license.unity.cn/update/poll?cmd=2&tx_id=dd555\r\n0490f56401a92752dbea2206dc5) failed [400 Bad Request]: Bad ULF signature - suspect foul play,Token not found in cache)\r\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\unity_license_test.log:16:[Licensing::Client] Error: Code 500 while updating lic\r\nense in client (status: Unable to update licenses. Errors: Request (POST https://license.unity.cn/update/poll?cmd=2&tx_\r\nid=dd5550490f56401a92752dbea2206dc5) failed [400 Bad Request]: Bad ULF signature - suspect foul play,Token not found in\r\n cache)\r\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\unity_license_test.log:19:[Licensing::Client] Successfully resolved entitlements\r\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\unity_license_test.log:20:[Licensing::Module] Serial number assigned to: \"F4-H1R\r\n5-BQNV-8DQZ-Q4V2-XXXX\"\r\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\unity_license_test.log:29:C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\unity_license_t\r\nest.log"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":31048,"aggregated":"Started Unity PID: 13664 at 05/15/2026 16:35:20\nKilled Unity after 30 seconds\n---Checking log for license status:\n\r\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\unity_license_test.log:4:[Licensing::Module] Error: LicensingClient has failed v\r\nalidation; ignoring\r\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\unity_license_test.log:11:[Licensing::Module] Successfully connected to Licensin\r\ngClient on channel: \"LicenseClient-yyzypublic\" (connect: 0.00s, validation: 0.02s, handshake: 0.52s)\r\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\unity_license_test.log:12:[Licensing::IpcConnector] Successfully connected to th\r\ne License Notification on channel: \"LicenseClient-yyzypublic-notifications\"\r\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\unity_license_test.log:13:Entitlement-based licensing initiated\r\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\unity_license_test.log:14:[Licensing::Module] Error: Access token is unavailable\r\n; failed to update\r\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\unity_license_test.log:15:[Licensing::Client] Error: Code 500 while processing r\r\nequest (status: Unable to update licenses. Errors: Request (POST https://license.unity.cn/update/poll?cmd=2&tx_id=dd555\r\n0490f56401a92752dbea2206dc5) failed [400 Bad Request]: Bad ULF signature - suspect foul play,Token not found in cache)\r\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\unity_license_test.log:16:[Licensing::Client] Error: Code 500 while updating lic\r\nense in client (status: Unable to update licenses. Errors: Request (POST https://license.unity.cn/update/poll?cmd=2&tx_\r\nid=dd5550490f56401a92752dbea2206dc5) failed [400 Bad Request]: Bad ULF signature - suspect foul play,Token not found in\r\n cache)\r\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\unity_license_test.log:19:[Licensing::Client] Successfully resolved entitlements\r\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\unity_license_test.log:20:[Licensing::Module] Serial number assigned to: \"F4-H1R\r\n5-BQNV-8DQZ-Q4V2-XXXX\"\r\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\unity_license_test.log:29:C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\unity_license_t\r\nest.log","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778834150599}}
{"type":"message","id":"303bf3dd","parentId":"7038db0c","timestamp":"2026-05-15T08:35:56.911Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! In GUI mode, the license still shows \"Access token is unavailable\" and \"Bad ULF signature - suspect foul play\", but then it still says \"Serial number assigned to: F4-H1R5-BQNV-8DQZ-Q4V2-XXXX\" and \"Successfully resolved entitlements\".\n\nBut then the log ends at line 29 with the log path - no \"Error: License is not active\" or \"No valid license\" message. So in GUI mode, the license was accepted! The difference is the headless entitlement - `com.unity.editor.headless` is not active.\n\nThis is a known Unity licensing issue: the license doesn't include the headless (batchmode) entitlement. The user needs to upgrade their Unity plan or contact Unity support.\n\nBut wait - the earlier run at 15:20 worked! The bat file ran Unity with `-batchmode` and it worked (the pipeline ran for 13+ minutes and wrote a 37MB log). So the headless entitlement WAS active at 15:20.\n\nWhat changed between 15:20 and now? The pipeline crashed at 15:34. When the pipeline crashed (Unity process 17676 exited abnormally), it might have corrupted the license state. Then when we tried to run again, the license was no longer valid for headless mode.\n\nLet me check the log from the GUI run more carefully to see if the license was actually fully valid.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_X6g0wnREhKAN4CPhdUH99795","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Content \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\unity_license_test.log\" -Raw"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":746,"output":371,"cacheRead":61440,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62557,"cost":{"input":0.00010444000000000001,"output":0.00010388,"cacheRead":0.00172032,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0019286400000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778834150