{"type":"message","id":"eb82410f","parentId":"1d17e5f5","timestamp":"2026-05-15T08:36:07.323Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, I see the difference!\n\nIn the GUI mode (BatchMode: 0):\n- `BatchMode: 0, IsHumanControllingUs: 1, StartBugReporterOnCrash: 1, Is64bit: 1, IsPro: 1`\n- It says `Serial number assigned` and no license error\n- The licensing client used is the HUB's version: `C:/Program Files/Unity Hub/UnityLicensingClient_V1/Unity.Licensing.Client.exe` (PID 18100)\n\nIn the batchmode run (from earlier):\n- `BatchMode: 1, IsHumanControllingUs: 0, StartBugReporterOnCrash: 0, Is64bit: 1, IsPro: 0`\n- The licensing client used is the BUNDLED version: `C:/Program Files/Unity/Hub/Editor/2020.3.49f1/Editor/Data/Resources/Licensing/Client/Unity.Licensing.Client.exe`\n\nThe key difference:\n1. **GUI mode**: Uses Hub's licensing client (v1.13.1), license works (Pro: 1)\n2. **Batchmode**: Uses bundled licensing client (v1.12.1), license: `HasEntitlements will fail`, `IsPro: 0`\n\nSo the issue is:\n- The bundled licensing client (v1.12.1) cannot validate the license for the headless entitlement\n- The Hub's licensing client (v1.13.1) CAN validate the license\n\nAnd the previous run at 15:20 that DID work - let me check its log to see which licensing client it used.\n\nLooking back at the earlier log from 15:20:\n```\n[Licensing::IpcConnector] Successfully connected to the License Client on channel: \"LicenseClient-yyzypublic\"\n[Licensing::Client] Error: Code 1 while verifying Licensing Client signature (process Id: 6764, path: \"C:/Program Files/Unity Hub/UnityLicensingClient_V1/Unity.Licensing.Client.exe\")\n```\n\nIt connected to the Hub's licensing client (PID 6764, path includes Hub). And it showed `IsPro: 1` and the serial was assigned. And it worked!\n\nBut now, the bundled licensing client starts first and doesn't connect to the Hub's one. The issue is specifically with the editor's bundled licensing client.\n\nThe reason the bundled licensing client starts instead of the Hub's one could be:\n1. The licensing client was stopped/killed earlier when I killed all Unity processes\n2. The Hub's licensing client needs to be running in advance\n\nActually wait - when I started the GUI version, the Hub's licensing client (PID 18100) was already running. When I started batchmode, it used the bundled one. The key is that in the successful run at 15:20, the Hub's licensing client was already running from before, and the batchmode Unity connected to it.\n\nBut in my current attempts, the Hub's licensing client is also running (I started Unity Hub). So why is batchmode not connecting to it?\n\nLet me check the batchmode log from the current run more carefully:","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_LpxHyIUfZXECHoHNHTiu6722","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Content \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log\" -Raw"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":942,"output":745,"cacheRead":62464,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64151,"cost":{"input":0.00013188000000000002,"output":0.0002086,"cacheRead":0.001748992,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.002089472}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778834157606,"responseId":"37ab34d6-9a4b-49af-9b61-1636e4973cda"}}
