  Machine Id:              LZAwQTvCYUKt/YECOewP4bDJVRk=\r\n[Licensing::Module] Successfully connected to LicensingClient on channel: \"LicenseClient-yyzypublic\" (connect: 0.49s, validation: 0.03s, handshake: 0.02s)\r\n[Licensing::IpcConnector] Successfully connected to the License Notification on channel: \"LicenseClient-yyzypublic-notifications\"\r\n[Licensing::Module] Connected to LicensingClient (PId: 18252, launch time: 0.01, total connection time: 0.54s)\r\nEntitlement-based licensing initiated\r\n[Licensing::Module] Error: Access token is unavailable; failed to update\r\n[Licensing::Client] Error: Code 500 while processing request (status: Unable to update licenses. Errors: Cannot load ULF license: The digital signature is invalid.,Token not found in cache)\r\n[Licensing::Client] Error: Code 500 while updating license in client (status: Unable to update licenses. Errors: Cannot load ULF license: The digital signature is invalid.,Token not found in cache)\r\nBuilt from '2020.3/china_unity/release' branch; Version is '2020.3.49f1c1 (9f87e50ef29c) revision 10455013'; Using compiler version '192528614'; Build Type 'Release'\r\nOS: 'Windows 11  (10.0.22631) 64bit Enterprise' Language: 'zh' Physical Memory: 32581 MB\r\n[Licensing::Client] Successfully resolved entitlements\r\n[Licensing::Module] Error: License is not active (com.unity.editor.headless). HasEntitlements will fail.\r\nBatchMode: 1, IsHumanControllingUs: 0, StartBugReporterOnCrash: 0, Is64bit: 1, IsPro: 0\r\nNo valid Unity Editor license found. Please activate your license.\r\nExiting without the bug reporter. Application will terminate with return code 1","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778834168003}}
{"type":"message","id":"e252eeb3","parentId":"becd3d23","timestamp":"2026-05-15T08:36:17.925Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can clearly see the problem:\n\n```\n[Licensing::Module] Trying to connect to existing licensing client channel...\n[Licensing::IpcConnector] Connection attempt to the License Client on channel: \"LicenseClient-yyzypublic\" failed because channel doesn't exist; code: \"0x80000002\"\n[Licensing::Module] Successfully launched the LicensingClient (PId: 18252)\n[Licensing::IpcConnector] Successfully connected to the License Client on channel: \"LicenseClient-yyzypublic\"\n[Licensing::Client] Error: Code 10 while verifying Licensing Client signature (process Id: 18252, path: \"C:/Program Files/Unity/Hub/Editor/2020.3.49f1/Editor/Data/Resources/Licensing/Client/Unity.Licensing.Client.exe\")\n```\n\nThe key sequence:\n1. Unity tries to connect to existing licensing client channel \"LicenseClient-yyzypublic\" - FAILS (channel doesn't exist)\n2. Unity LAUNCHES its own bundled licensing client (PID 18252) from `...Editor/Data/Resources/Licensing/Client/`\n3. The bundled client uses version 1.12.1 which reports \"Cannot load ULF license: The digital signature is invalid\"\n4. Result: \"Error: License is not active (com.unity.editor.headless). HasEntitlements will fail.\"\n\nIn the successful run at 15:20:\n```\n[Licensing::Module] Trying to connect to existing licensing client channel...\n[Licensing::IpcConnector] Successfully connected to the License Client on channel: \"LicenseClient-yyzypublic\"\n[Licensing::Client] Error: Code 1 while verifying Licensing Client signature (process Id: 6764, path: \"C:/Program Files/Unity Hub/UnityLicensingClient_V1/Unity.Licensing.Client.exe\")\n```\n\nThe key difference:\n1. Connection to channel \"LicenseClient-yyzypublic\" **SUCCEEDED** (Hub's licensing client was already running)\n2. It connected to the Hub's licensing client v1.13.1\n3. Even though there was a Code 1 signature verification error, it was \"ignored\" and continued\n4. Result: \"Serial number assigned\" and `IsPro: 1`\n\nSo the fix is to ensure the Hub's licensing client is already running BEFORE Unity starts in batchmode. The Hub's licensing client creates the IPC channel \"LicenseClient-yyzypublic\" that Unity connects to.\n\nWhen I killed all Unity processes earlier (including the Hub's licensing client), I broke this connection. I need to restart the Hub's licensing client before running the bat file.\n\nLet me start the Hub's licensing client first, then run the bat file.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_30H4K6ZeZiYcP00XyErP6138","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# First, ensure no editor-bundled licensing client is running\nGet-Process -Name \"Unity.Licensing.Client\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Where-Object { $_.StartTime -gt (Get-Date \"2026-05-15 16:30:00\") } | Stop-Process -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\nStart-Sleep -Seconds 2\n\n# Start the Hub's licensing client in the background to create the IPC channel\n# The Hub's licensing client path\n$hubLicClient = \"C:\\Program Files\\Unity Hub\\UnityLicensingClient_V1\\Unity.Licensing.Client.exe\"\n\n# Start it silently - it will create the IPC channel\n$p = Start-Process -FilePath $hubLicClient -WindowStyle Hidden -PassThru\nWrite-Host \"Started Hub Licensing Client PID: $($p.Id) at $(Get-Date)\"\nStart-Sleep -Seconds 3\n\n# Verify it's running\nGet-Process -Name \"Unity.Licensing.Client\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Id, StartTime, ProcessName\n\nWrite-Host \"Now running Unity pipeline...\"\n\n# Now run the build pipeline bat file\n\"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\RunBuildPipelineHotUpdate.bat\" 2>&1","timeout":60,"yieldMs":30000}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":796,"output":944,"cacheRead":64128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65868,"cost":{"input":0.00011144,"output":0.00026432,"cacheRead":0.001795584,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.002171344}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778834168005,"responseId":"329f15e7-853b-457f-bf48-3294a0241865"}}
