{"type":"message","id":"47f4ba90","parentId":"f2eca1a6","timestamp":"2026-05-15T08:36:33.457Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Same issue - still using the old log from 16:31. The bat file ran but the license still failed. Let me check if the Hub's licensing client was connected properly by checking its process, or if there's something else going on.\n\nActually, I notice the log file timestamp didn't change (16:31:08). This means Unity didn't even overwrite the log file - it ran with the same log file and probably the same result. But wait, the log file content starts from the beginning... The Unity batchmode run created a new log file and the old one was overwritten.\n\nActually no - the length is 2608 bytes which is exactly the same as before. The content I see is the same as before. This means Unity wrote the exact same log content to the file (overwriting it).\n\nLet me check the licensing client process more carefully.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_cg6tcwSPEAtcPG2LbHZ11757","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check which licensing client process is running\nGet-CimInstance Win32_Process -Filter \"Name='Unity.Licensing.Client.exe'\" | Select-Object ProcessId, CommandLine, CreationDate | Format-List\n\nWrite-Host \"---\"\n\n# Check if the IPC channel exists\n$channelPath = \"\\\\.\\pipe\\LicenseClient-yyzypublic\"\nif ([System.IO.Directory]::Exists($channelPath)) {\n    Write-Host \"IPC channel exists\"\n} else {\n    Write-Host \"Checking for IPC via named pipe...\"\n    # Try to check named pipes\n    [System.IO.Directory]::GetFiles(\"\\\\.\\pipe\\\") | Where-Object { $_ -like \"*License*\" }\n}"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":402,"output":371,"cacheRead":66048,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66821,"cost":{"input":0.00005628,"output":0.00010388,"cacheRead":0.001849344,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.002009504}},"stopR