{"type":"message","id":"9c864053","parentId":"10b6425c","timestamp":"2026-05-15T08:36:41.765Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Hub's licensing client is running with the correct named pipe `Unity-LicenseClient-yyzypublic`. But Unity's batchmode keeps launching its OWN licensing client.\n\nWait - looking at the batchmode Unity log from the previous successful run:\n```\n[Licensing::IpcConnector] Successfully connected to the License Client on channel: \"LicenseClient-yyzypublic\"\n```\n\nAnd from the failed run:\n```\n[Licensing::IpcConnector] Connection attempt to the License Client on channel: \"LicenseClient-yyzypublic\" failed because channel doesn't exist; code: \"0x80000002\"\n```\n\nThe channel name is different from the pipe name! The named pipe is `Unity-LicenseClient-yyzypublic` but the connection attempt uses `LicenseClient-yyzypublic` (without \"Unity-\" prefix).\n\nWait, but the Hub's licensing client cmdline shows `--namedPipe Unity-LicenseClient-yyzypublic`. But the earlier successful run showed `LicenseClient-yyzypublic` without the \"Unity-\" prefix. Maybe Unity strips the prefix internally.\n\nLet me check - maybe there's a timing issue. The Hub's licensing client might take a few seconds to fully start and create the IPC channel. Let me wait longer before running Unity.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_2gyJqvL77wzAvSPvW8te1817","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Kill existing Unity processes (editor batchmode and licensing)\nGet-Process -Name \"Unity\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Stop-Process -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\nStart-Sleep -Seconds 1\n\n# Ensure Hub's licensing client is running properly\n$hubLicClient = \"C:\\Program Files\\Unity Hub\\UnityLicensingClient_V1\\Unity.Licensing.Client.exe\"\n\n# Check if already running\n$existing = Get-Process -Name \"Unity.Licensing.Client\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Where-Object { $_.StartTime -gt (Get-Date \"2026-05-15 16:35:00\") }\nif (-not $existing) {\n    $p = Start-Process -FilePath $hubLicClient -WindowStyle Hidden -PassThru\n    Write-Host \"Started Hub Licensing Client PID: $($p.Id)\"\n} else {\n    Write-Host \"Hub Licensing Client already running: PID $($existing.Id)\"\n}\n\n# Wait for the licensing client to fully initialize\nStart-Sleep -Seconds 10\n\n# Verify the named pipe exists\n$pipes = [System.IO.Directory]::GetFiles(\"\\\\.\\pipe\\\") | Where-Object { $_ -like \"*License*\" }\nWrite-Host \"Licensing pipes:\" \n$pipes | ForEach-Object { Write-Host \"  $_\" }\n\nWrite-Host \"\"\nWrite-Host \"Now running Unity pipeline...\"\nWrite-Host \"\"\n\n# Run the bat file\n\"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\RunBuildPipelineHotUpdate.bat\" 2>&1","timeout":60,"yieldMs":30000}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":139,"output":687,"cacheRead":66816,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67642,"cost":{"input":0.00001946,"output":0.00019236,"cacheRead":0.001870848,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.002082668}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778834194437,"responseId":"ee69904f-5a7d-4627-84a5-49a2442ed666"}}
